title: Chhetri scores twice as Mumbai outclass Delhi
text:
Mumbai, October 21
Sunil Chhetri finally found his goal-scoring touch with a brace as Mumbai City beat Delhi Dynamos 2-0 to notch up their maiden win in the Indian Super League here today. The Indian football team captain was set up by Haitian Sony Norde on both the occasions. The victory, after two losses and a draw, boosted their points tally to four. Mumbai, who had scored only one goal so far, found the mark in the 13th minute after a delightful one-two between Norde and Chhetri. Chhetri scored the second with a deft low shot into the left corner after his strike partner had run through three defenders to lay it up for him, much to the delight of the small crowd. â€” PTI
